flowchart TD
    A["src/backend/routers/agent.py::runtime_agent_run\nTrigger: POST /api/agents/run\nData: RuntimeAgentRunRequest {query, thread_id?, user_id?, checkpoint_id?}\nWhy: accept runtime memory/checkpoint context"] --> B["src/backend/services/agent_service.py::run_runtime_agent\nTrigger: router call\nData: validated payload + DB session\nWhy: keep API response contract stable while delegating execution"]

    B --> C["src/backend/agents/langgraph_agent.py::LangGraphAgentScaffold.run\nTrigger: service invokes runtime scaffold\nData: payload + SQLAlchemy session\nWhy: orchestrate decomposition/retrieval/validation/synthesis + persistence"]

    C --> D["DeepAgentPersistenceStore.read_memories\nTrigger: run() pre-execution memory routing\nData: namespace=(user_id, \"memories\"), query, limit\nWhy: inject prior user-scoped memory context before synthesis"]

    C --> E["Pipeline steps\nFunctions: decompose_query -> assign_tools_to_sub_queries -> execute_subquery_retrievals -> validate_retrieval_results -> synthesize_answer\nData: sub_queries, assignments, retrievals, validations, output\nWhy: deterministic scaffold orchestration"]

    E --> F["DeepAgentPersistenceStore.write_memory\nTrigger: run() after synthesis\nData: deterministic value {kind, query, summary}\nWhy: persist reusable cross-thread memory for same user namespace"]

    E --> G["DeepAgentPersistenceStore.persist_thread_checkpoint\nTrigger: run() after synthesis\nData: thread_id + checkpoint_id? + query/output\nWhy: preserve per-thread replay/time-travel history"]

    D --> H["graph_state.graph.execution.persistence\nFields: memory_reads_before_run, store_namespace, store_entry_count_before_run\nWhy: expose memory-read behavior for smoke verification"]
    F --> H
    G --> H

    C --> I["graph_state.timeline\nEvents: memory.read(started/completed), synthesis(completed), memory.write(started/completed)\nWhy: make trigger ordering observable in tests"]

    N1["Decision: use deterministic memory_id = sha256(sorted JSON payload)\nTradeoff: identical inputs deduplicate memory entries; stable IDs simplify deterministic tests."] --- F
    N2["Decision: read memories before decomposition in scaffold mode\nTradeoff: simple explicit routing now; later semantic filtering can use query argument without API changes."] --- D
